  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nanvil 0.1.0 (1a56901 2023-02-15T00:04:36.717767498Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil --prune-history 100 --steps-tracing --silent --hardfork berlin --port 41379\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe `eth_sendTransaction` JSON-RPC call does not seem to accept the `chainId` field. Setting this field raises\r\n```\r\n{'code': -32602, 'message': 'data did not match any variant of untagged enum EthRpcCall'}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAccording to [EIP-1559](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1559), `chainId` can be/should be set in type 1 (EIP-2930) and type 2 (EIP-1559) transactions.\r\n\r\nExample JSON-RPC call:\r\n```\r\n{'jsonrpc': '2.0', 'method': 'eth_sendUnsignedTransaction', 'params': [{'type': '0x1', 'nonce': '0x0', 'to': '0x70997970c51812dc3a010c7d01b50e0d17dc79c8', 'from': '0xf39fd6e51aad88f6f4ce6ab8827279cfffb92266', 'gas': '0x1c9c380', 'value': '0x1', 'data': '0x', 'gasPrice': '0x0', 'accessList': [], 'chainId': '0x7a69'}], 'id': 8}\r\n```",
